[SN]TITLE[SN]
Harrogate driver Samuel Cooper banned for 'dangerous stunts'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have released a video of a 25-year-old who drove around a supermarket car park with three other youths hanging from his car.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
10 October 2014 Last updated at 16:54 BST
CCTV captured Samuel Cooper doing "dangerous stunts" in Asda car park on Bower Road, Harrogate.
Appearing at Harrogate Magistrates' Court, Cooper, of Verity Walk, Harrogate, admitted dangerous driving and driving without insurance.
He was banned from driving for 18 months and ordered to take an extended driving test.
